to use functions? Maybe I can just create interfaces without methods? I'm considering a Runnable function instead. There’s also the idea of using NativeObject with NativeFunction, but I can’t really test that right now. I just need to consider how NativeJavaObject.writeObject will work if it’s an adapter.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering naming conventions in Java**\\n\\nI’m thinking about Java source code and the use of public static nested classes. It raises questions about whether class names should include a dollar sign ($) in their string representations. There seems to be a specific rule regarding file names, stating that the dollar sign should never be used in test class or file names. I wonder how strictly that rule is applied and if there are any exceptions that I should consider.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Debugging Java tests**\\n\\nI’m considering that dynamic generation is likely causing an UnsupportedFeatureError directly from defineClass. That’s not ideal, but I need to implement some assertions. I think I'll use AssertJ for that. Additionally, I might want to update the public access level in RhinoTest? That seems necessary. To handle this effectively, I’ll make sure to use the edit function to implement these changes. Let's see how this unfolds!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_inK7q30CZhBvH00YjL21tDze|fc_05e4938072b3cd5a0169f51cb74c7081a3bf3f424e547d5375", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/JavaAdapterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mozilla.rhino;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\n\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Context;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.ContextFactory;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Scriptable;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.ScriptableObject;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.serialize.ScriptableInputStream;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.serialize.ScriptableOutputStream;\n\npublic class JavaAdapterTest {\n    @Test\n    void createsAdapterForInterfaceAndOverridableSuperclassMethods() throws Exception {\n        runAllowingNativeImageUnsupportedClassGeneration(() -> {\n            Context context = ContextFactory.getGlobal().enterContext();\n            try {\n                Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n                String source = \"\"\"\n                        var adapter = new JavaAdapter(%s, java.lang.Comparable, {\n                            greet: function(name) {\n                                return 'hello, ' + name;\n                            }\n                        });\n                        adapter.greet('rhino') + ':' + adapter.compareTo('ignored');\n                        \"\"\".formatted(ComparableGreeter.class.getName());\n\n                Object result = context.evaluateString(scope, source, \"java-adapter-create\", 1, null);\n\n                assertThat(Context.toString(result)).isEqualTo(\"hello, rhino:7\");\n            } finally {\n                Context.exit();\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void serializesAndRestoresAdapterWrapper() throws Exception {\n        runAllowingNativeImageUnsupportedClassGeneration(() -> {\n            Context context = ContextFactory.getGlobal().enterContext();\n            context.setOptimizationLevel(-1);\n            try {\n                Scriptable scope = context.initStandardObjects();\n                Scriptable adapter = (Scriptable) context.evaluateString(scope, \"\"\"\n                        new JavaAdapter(java.lang.Runnable, {\n                            count: 0,\n                            run: function() {\n                                this.count = this.count + 1;\n                            },\n                            value: function() {\n                                return this.count;\n                            }\n                        });\n                        \"\"\", \"java-adapter-serialize\", 1, null);\n\n                ByteArrayOutputStream buffer = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n                try (ScriptableOutputStream output = new ScriptableOutputStream(buffer, scope)) {\n                    output.writeObject(adapter);\n                }\n\n                Object restored;\n                try (ScriptableInputStream input = new ScriptableInputStream(\n                        new ByteArrayInputStream(buffer.toByteArray()),\n                        scope\n                )) {\n                    restored = input.readObject();\n                }\n\n                ScriptableObject.putProperty(scope, \"adapter\", restored);\n                Object result = context.evaluateString(scope, \"\"\"\n                        adapter.run();\n                        adapter.run();\n                        adapter.value();\n                        \"\"\", \"java-adapter-restored\", 1, null);\n\n                assertThat(Context.toNumber(result)).isEqualTo(2.0d);\n            } finally {\n                Context.exit();\n            }\n        });\n    }\n\n    @FunctionalInterface\n    private interface ThrowingRunnable {\n        void run() throws Exception;\n    }\n\n    private static void runAllowingNativeImageUnsupportedClassGeneration(ThrowingRunnable action) throws Exception {\n        try {\n            action.run();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ComparableGreeter implements Comparable<Object> {\n        public String greet(String name) {\n            return \"base \" + name;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int compareTo(Object other) {\n            return 7;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1268, "output": 2806, "cacheRead": 59904, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63978, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777671323944, "responseId": "resp_05e4938072b3cd5a0169f51c9c666481a38abb6d3bed68bea2"}}
